Mirror operations: sync, restore, drill, prefixes

Usage: sleet mirror <COMMAND>

Commands:
  sync      Run a single sync pass for one (database, target), regardless of the target's mode; prunes afterward when retention is set
  restore   Copy one restore point's closure from a backup into an empty destination root and commit it
  drill     Restore drill: restore a point from the target's destination into a scratch root, open it, and scan every key. Proves the backup restores end to end
  prefixes  Emit the anchored key-prefix filter lists an external replication service needs for one (database, target)
  help      Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help  Print help
